  "prompt": "Why do people throw garbage on the roads, corners, empty spaces or rather wherever they find a place?",
  "response": "People litter for various psychological, social, and environmental reasons:\n\n1. Psychological factors:\n- Lack of personal responsibility\n- Laziness\n- Convenience\n- Low environmental consciousness\n- Absence of immediate consequences\n\n2. Social factors:\n- Poor civic sense\n- Cultural habits\n- Lack of public awareness\n- Absence of strict enforcement\n- Limited garbage disposal infrastructure\n- No sense of community ownership\n\n3. Systemic issues:\n- Insufficient public trash bins\n- Irregular garbage collection\n- Poor waste management systems\n- Limited public education about environmental impact\n\n4. Attitudinal reasons:\n- Believing someone else will clean it\n- Thinking small amounts of trash don't matter\n- Indifference towards public spaces\n- Lack of pride in surroundings\n\n5. Economic factors:\n- Limited resources for proper waste disposal\n- Inadequate municipal services\n- Cost of proper disposal\n\n6. Behavioral patterns:\n- Learned behavior from family/community\n- Following existing littering trends\n- Lack of role models practicing responsible disposal\n\nSolutions require:\n- Strong awareness campaigns\n- Strict legal penalties\n- Environmental education\n- Improved waste management infrastructure\n- Community engagement\n- Individual behavioral changes\n\nCreating a clean environment requires collective responsibility and individual commitment.",
